    "data": { "title": "Question 1: Newton's First Law", "open": false },
    "children": [
      {
        "id": "qc-6-1",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "data": { "text": "An object at rest stays at rest and an object in motion stays in motion with the same speed and in the same direction unless acted upon by an unbalanced force." }
      },
      {
        "id": "qc-6-2",
        "type": "code",
        "data": {
          "language": "text",
          "text": "A) Force causes motion\nB) Inertia resists changes in motion\nC) Acceleration is proportional to mass\nD) Every action has an equal reaction"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "qc-6-3",
        "type": "callout",
        "data": { "icon": "✅", "text": "Correct answer: B. Newton's First Law is also known as the Law of Inertia." }
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "qc-7",
    "type": "toggle",
    "data": { "title": "Question 2: Kinetic Energy", "open": false },
    "children": [
      {
        "id": "qc-7-1",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "data": { "text": "What is the kinetic energy of a 2 kg object moving at 3 m/s?" }
      },
      {
        "id": "qc-7-2",
        "type": "code",
        "data": {
          "language": "text",
          "text": "A) 3 J\nB) 6 J\nC) 9 J\nD) 18 J"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "qc-7-3",
        "type": "callout",
        "data": { "icon": "✅", "text": "Correct answer: C. KE = ½mv² = ½ × 2 × 9 = 9 J." }
      }
    ]
  },
